📝 C1: Simple GCD Problem — Proper Notes
🧠 1. Core Observation (MOST IMPORTANT)

👉 We don’t need all subarrays

If all adjacent GCDs are preserved, then all subarray GCDs are preserved.

So only care about:

gcd(a[i-1], a[i])
⚙️ 2. Operation Meaning

We change:

a[i] → m   (m < a[i])

But must keep:

gcd(a[i-1], m) = gcd(a[i-1], a[i])
gcd(m, a[i+1]) = gcd(a[i], a[i+1])
🔥 3. Key Intuition (VERY IMPORTANT)

Let:

A = gcd(a[i-1], a[i])
B = gcd(a[i], a[i+1])

Then:

m must be divisible by A
m must be divisible by B

👉 So:

m must be a common multiple of A and B

👉 Smallest such value:

m = lcm(A, B)
🎯 4. Final Condition

We need:

m < a[i]

So:

lcm(A, B) < a[i]

✔️ If true → operation possible
❌ Else → not possible

⚠️ 5. Edge Cases
🔹 First element
gcd(a[0], a[1]) < a[0]
🔹 Last element
gcd(a[n-2], a[n-1]) < a[n-1]
🧠 6. Why LCM? (Memory Trick)

GCD conditions force divisibility →
Multiple constraints → take LCM

⚡ 7. Patterns to Recognize
❌ Cannot change when:
lcm(A, B) == a[i]
✅ Can change when:
lcm(A, B) < a[i]
🔥 Special Case (important)

If:

a[i-1] | a[i] | a[i+1]

Then:

lcm = a[i]

👉 So no change possible

🚀 8. Final Code (Contest Ready)
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define ll long long

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while(t--) {
        int n;
        cin >> n;

        vector<ll> a(n);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) cin >> a[i];

        int ans = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if(i == 0) {
                if(gcd(a[0], a[1]) < a[0]) ans++;
            }
            else if(i == n - 1) {
                if(gcd(a[n-2], a[n-1]) < a[n-1]) ans++;
            }
            else {
                ll A = gcd(a[i-1], a[i]);
                ll B = gcd(a[i], a[i+1]);

                ll L = lcm(A, B);

                if(L < a[i]) ans++;
            }
        }

        cout << ans << "\n";
    }
}
🧠 9. Mental Template (for contests)

When you see:

GCD of subarrays
Modify elements

👉 Think:

“Can I reduce to adjacent pairs?”
“What constraints does GCD impose?”
“Multiple constraints → LCM”
“Check smallest valid value”
💥 Final One-Line Summary

Replace a[i] with smallest valid value = lcm(A,B)
If that is smaller → operation possible
